title: UMLS Release QA
note1: This application compares different versions of the UMLS Metathesaurus for QA purposes. Use the UMLS Metathesaurus Full Subset. The META folder for the current release and the previous release must be in the releases folder (e.g. releases/2025AA/META). The reports take some time to run.
note2: Ultimately we want to do two things with this QA system: -Check for obvious issues with the release. -Identify major changes that might be work mentioning in release notes.

lineCountNotes.MRCONSO.RRF: Counts are expected to increase for sources that were updated. Note any decreases or large increases.
lineCountNotes.MRDEF.RRF: Note any decreases or large increases.
lineCountNotes.MRDOC.RRF: New and removed languages, relations, and attributes will appear here. New release rows will also appear. Note anything unusual.
lineCountNotes.MRFILES.RRF: This generally only changes if we add a new language - a new word index will be generated for that language.
lineCountNotes.MRRANK.RRF: Note any changes in ranking order. Added or removed rows will be listed.
lineCountNotes.MRREL.RRF: Note any decreases or large increases.
lineCountNotes.MRSAT.RRF: Note any decreases or large increases.
lineCountNotes.MRXW_ARA.RRF: Translation word indexes. Expect small increases. Decreases do happen if translations drop content, but these will usually increase or stay the same.

reportInstructions.MRCOLS: This will typically not change unless a file is added or removed. A new language could result in a word index being added, such as in the case of Icelandic in 2025AA.
